HTTP/1.0 503 Service Unavailable
Cache-Control: no-cache
Connection: close
Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>App not running — Vibe Appliance emergency access</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
         max-width: 36rem; margin: 4rem auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; color: #2a2520;
         background: #faf7f2; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #6b4423; }
  p { line-height: 1.55; }
  code { background: #efe9df; padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 0.95em; }
  .note { color: #8a7860; font-size: 0.9em; margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid #e0d8c8;
          padding-top: 1rem; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>App not running</h1>
<p>You reached the Vibe Appliance <strong>emergency access</strong> port for an app
that isn't currently enabled (or its container is down).</p>
<p>Open the admin console at <code>https://admin.&lt;your-server&gt;/admin</code> to
enable the app or check its status. The admin URL was printed during
installation — see <code>/opt/vibe/CREDENTIALS.txt</code> on the host if
you've forgotten it.</p>
<p class="note">This is plain HTTP on a non-standard port. Browsers may flag
it as insecure — that's expected. Emergency access is gated to your LAN
or Tailscale network and exists only for staff use when the primary
HTTPS routing is broken.</p>
</body>
</html>
